 <br>
If you go in there,it's different even if you killed off part/all of what's in there. New monsters have moved into the halls you visited prior. Uber_named_mob_01 isn't sitting in the same spot waiting for you to gank him.<br>
 <br>
I went into Mistmoore last night with PN. We finally ended up at the end, with a line of vampires covering the one we came to assassinate. We figured it out with a stalking probe (go Kubie!) and pacified our way to the boss-and despite Kubie getting charmed and beating up a certain shaman, we finished it with time to spare. And messed with a few bitten victims (sorry about the spiders there, but at least we found an augment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) and found another big fellow up there.<br>
 <br>
Mission accomplished, party leaves victorious....<br>
 <br>
And Mistmoore's other minions fill in the space, some of the bitten victims rise up as new undead, and the next time we come there,things will be different...<br>
<br>
...as opposed to the same dungeon with the same monsters over and over and over and over and respawning and camping the named again and again for X drop till you puke.<br>
<br>
That's a dungeon for you.<br>
<br>
