<br>
At eq toolbox.com you can download maps for the spawned zones.  Which leads me to believe the zones themselves are in fact real (in a gaming sense anyway).  There are just a certain number of instances that vary per adventure.  It's kind of like a standardized test where they hand out a form A, B, and C. It's all the same test, but there are three formats to discourage cheating.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I did a collection mission at Mistmoore last night. It was fun, completed it in plenty of time to go look around and mop up stragglers.  Only two complaints. First, on the way out of the dungeon, after we'd completed the mission the group tripped a poison trap at the zone line that almost killed all of us after we zoned into LFAY.  Second for completion of our mission, at level 31, I received a grand total of...are your ready for this?...drumroll.... 2 adventure points! (CHEERS! THE CROWD GOES WILD).  Where on earth will I spend all those points :-/ <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=776125" target="top">-Jahvah</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
