I think there are a limited number of very large zones, but if you look carfully, you'll see that your particular dungeon has a lot of closed passages.<br>
I think passages are 'plugged' differently each time it's 'created', isolating a small part of the zone wich is used for your adventure.<br>
A zone-in area and a target area are placed randomly within the dungeon and then a somewhat random path between them is made by turning some doorways into walls.<br>
Then a balanced number of enemies is placed between the two points.<br>
<br>
That's my theory <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
You can probably map the whole 'big zone', but it would be worthless since you don't know wich passages will be sealed each time.<br>
